  "texts": [
    "In this feature extraction process, we first re-referenced all channels within each 64-contact grid to a common-average reference (CAR filtering), excluding channels with poor signal quality in any training session.",
    "Next, we selected all channels that had previously shown significant high-gamma responses during the syllable repetition task described above.",
    "This included 64 channels (Supplementary Fig.",
    "S2, channels with blue outlines) across motor, premotor and somatosensory cortices, including the dorsal laryngeal area.",
    "From here, we applied two IIR Butterworth filters (both with filter order 8) to extract the high-gamma band in the range of 70 to 170 Hz while subsequently attenuating the first harmonic (118-122 Hz) of the line noise."
  ],
  "correct_citations": []
}